  "description": [
    "THE BROWNING CHIEF John E Davies Editor and Owner A weekly newspaper published every Friday at Browning Glacier County Montana Entered as 2nd class matter July 13 1931 at the postoffice at Browning Montana under act of March 3 1879 Subscription 200 year in advance TAKING A CLOSER LOOK Most of Americas mistakes in the Far East are due to overesti mating the might of western arms and underestimating the power of Asian ideas This is the key to much that has happened in China In Korea inadequate measures were taken to guard the young republic Then it was said that the North Koreans could be stopped by American air and sea power This was fol lowed by a complete misjudgment of Chinas vital interest in Korea Now Russias deep concern with Manchuria is being shrugged off Both General Marshall and General MacArthur a p p e a r to underestimate Chinese and Russian interest in the area General MacArthur believes Russia would not retaliate should United Nations forces bomb Manchuria General Marshall in the Senate hearings opposed this estimate but held that UN aims can be achieved in Korea by con tinuing to destroy the eream of Chinas trained"
  ],
